'''Blue Ash''' is a city in , , , just outside . The population was 12,513 at the .
Blue Ash is located at {{coor dms|39|14|50|N|84|22|34|W|city}} (39.247109, -84.376038){{GR|1}}.
According to the , the city has a total area of 7.7&nbsp;s (19.9&nbsp;), of which, 7.7&nbsp;square&nbsp;miles (19.8&nbsp;km²) of it is land and 0.13% is water.
As of the {{GR|2}} of 2000, there were 12,513 people, 4,990 households, and 3,468 families residing in the city. The  was 1,634.6 people per square mile (630.7/km²). There were 5,251 housing units at an average density of 686.0/sq&nbsp;mi (264.7/km²). The racial makeup of the city was 87.09% , 5.01% , 0.25% , 6.39% , 0.02% , 0.29% from , and 0.96% from two or more races.  or  of any race were 0.97% of the population.
There were 4,990 households out of which 32.7% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 57.2% were  living together, 9.4% had a female householder with no husband present, and 30.5% were non-families. 25.3% of all households were made up of individuals and 8.4% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.48 and the average family size was 3.01.
In the city the population was spread out with 25.4% under the age of 18, 6.4% from 18 to 24, 27.8% from 25 to 44, 26.1% from 45 to 64, and 14.2% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 39 years. For every 100 females there were 93.7 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 91.0 males.
The median income for a household in the city was $61,591, and the median income for a family was $69,494. Males had a median income of $52,743 versus $35,060 for females. The  for the city was $33,801. About 3.8% of families and 4.7% of the population were below the , including 6.8% of those under age 18 and 2.9% of those age 65 or over.
Blue Ash is mostly served by the . Private education is provided by  for high school boys,  is for high school girls.  serves grades k-12. Blue Ash is also home to Raymond Walters College, a satellite campus of .
Blue Ash offers three summer events each year:  Summerbration; Red, White, and Blue Ash; and Taste of Blue Ash. Red, White and Blue Ash is held on annually on July 4th and features the biggest  firework display in the region. The event also draws headline acts for a free concert before the fireworks. The  Band and  are slated to perform on July 4, 2008.   and  played in 2007. Other past performers include   in 2006,  in 2004,  in 2000 and 2003,  in 2002, and  in both 1998 and 1999.
The North America Information Technology division of  has headquarters in Blue Ash.
